Among the first readers who tweet us with the hidden hashtag, well raffle a quite extraordinary, smashing prize (and a couple of other Smashing extras):
  1. a roundtrip flight to New York, USA

I picked up one of the Livescribe pen/notebook combinations for my first conference. Its great as it records audio as you take notes and creates a file with the audio and what you wrote on the paper. Not only do you get the audio of the presentation but the Livescribe software will translate your written notes to electronic text. It even does a good job with my messy writing. This allowed me to dump all the presentations easily into the company documentation system to share. This system worked so well at the conference I began using it in most meetings.
